<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>The createRow method does not set default data based on the table metadata. Looking at the source it seems that it was intended, but the feature was never added:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$defaults = array_combine($this-&gt;_cols, array_fill(0, count($this-&gt;_cols), null));
$keys = array_flip($this-&gt;_cols);
$data = array_intersect_key($data, $keys);
$data = array_merge($defaults, $data);
</code></pre>

<p>The $defaults variable is currently just filled with nulls. Simple enough to add:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
$defaults = array_combine($this-&gt;_cols, array_fill(0, count($this-&gt;_cols), null));
foreach ($this-&gt;_cols as $col) {
    if (isset($this-&gt;_metadata[$col]['DEFAULT'])) {
        $defaults[$col] = $this-&gt;_metadata[$col]['DEFAULT'];
    }
}
</code></pre>

