            <p>I understand the objective of this feature (which has evolved from the initial report):  a new, unsaved Row object has fields missing, or uses the value {{Zend_Db_Expr('DEFAULT')}}, which doesn't have enough information to be useful.  Ideally, a developer wants all fields of the Row object to be populated with values, so he can read the fields and choose to change them before a newly created Row object has been saved.  Fields he has not specified in the initial {{createRow()}} call should be populated automatically with defaults, either from the table class or from the database metadata.</p>

